verbose_text: As growers begin to use " atoxigenic " strains of Aspergillus flavus to reduce the accumulation of aflatoxin in maize, it is important for them to understand that certain " atoxigenic " strains may help to reduce aflatoxins but may not do anything to reduce CPA accumulation in grain or, in a worst case, may actually lead to higher levels of CPA in treated grain.
